net.sf.click.extras.control
Class IntegerField

java.lang.Object
  net.sf.click.control.Field
      net.sf.click.control.TextField
          net.sf.click.extras.control.IntegerField
All Implemented Interfaces:
Control, Serializable
public class IntegerField
extends TextField

Provides a Integer Field control:   <input type='text'>.

Integer Field
IntegerField will validate the number when the control is processed and invoke the control listener if there is no parsing error.

The IntegerField uses a JavaScript onKeyPress() integerFilter() method to prevent users from entering invalid characters. To enable number key filtering reference the Form.getHtmlImports() object in the page template. For example: 

 <html>
  <head>
   $imports
  </head>
  <body>
   $form
  </body>
 </html>
See also W3C HTML reference INPUT

Malcolm Edgar

onProcess

public boolean onProcess()
Process the IntegerField submission. If the Integer value can be parsed the controls listener will be invoked.

A field error message is displayed if a validation error occurs. These messages are defined in the resource bundle: 

/click-control.properties

Error message bundle key names include:

  • field-required-error
  • integer-format-error
  • number-maxvalue-error
  • number-minvalue-error

See Also:
Control.onProcess()
